1
00:00:01,752 --> 00:00:03,921
[theme song playing]

2
00:01:27,004 --> 00:01:27,879
[alarm blaring]

3
00:01:28,005 --> 00:01:29,381
[Matsuda] What is this?

4
00:01:29,798 --> 00:01:31,300
[Watari grunts]

5
00:01:34,052 --> 00:01:35,721
[groaning]

6
00:01:40,851 --> 00:01:42,394
Everyone. Shiniga--

7
00:01:42,519 --> 00:01:43,812
[heartbeat]

8
00:02:02,497 --> 00:02:04,207
RENEWAL

9
00:02:04,333 --> 00:02:06,752
[L] Now, try to kill me!

10
00:02:07,377 --> 00:02:10,380
[L] Although this was announced
as a worldwide broadcast,

11
00:02:10,547 --> 00:02:14,926
the truth is, we are only broadcasting
in the Kanto region of Japan.

12
00:02:15,135 --> 00:02:18,722
In actuality, the first of your victims
was a suspect in Shinjuku.

13
00:02:18,889 --> 00:02:21,391
Furthermore, his crime
was only ever reported inside of Japan.

14
00:02:21,475 --> 00:02:22,893
[reporter] The suspect is now dead!

15
00:02:23,060 --> 00:02:25,729
I used that information
to deduce this much:

16
00:02:25,854 --> 00:02:27,147
You are in Japan,

17
00:02:27,606 --> 00:02:30,692
and your first victim
was little more than an experiment,

18
00:02:30,776 --> 00:02:33,445
which means that you haven’t been killing
for very long.

19
00:02:33,528 --> 00:02:35,113
KIRA TASK FORCE HEADQUARTERS

20
00:02:35,614 --> 00:02:40,077
Kira has found a way to obtain information
from the task force headquarters.

21
00:02:40,243 --> 00:02:42,579
There are 141 people in the police force

22
00:02:42,663 --> 00:02:45,832
who have access to classified information
regarding the investigation.

23
00:02:45,916 --> 00:02:49,211
I’m sure that somewhere in this list
of police officers,

24
00:02:49,336 --> 00:02:51,463
and the people closest to them…

25
00:02:51,713 --> 00:02:52,673
we will find our suspect

26
00:02:52,756 --> 00:02:54,966
SOICHIRO YAGAMI (48) DOB 7/12/59
DETECTIVE SUPERINTENDENT,

27
00:02:55,050 --> 00:02:58,303
FBI INVESTIGATION OF THOSE INVOLVED
WITH THE JAPANESE POLICE

28
00:02:58,428 --> 00:03:02,349
On December 14,
twelve FBI investigators enter Japan.

29
00:03:03,892 --> 00:03:06,061
Here we are on December 19th.

30
00:03:06,353 --> 00:03:07,854
Using prison inmates,

31
00:03:08,063 --> 00:03:09,773
Kira conducts experiments,

32
00:03:09,898 --> 00:03:11,983
manipulating his victims' actions
before they die.

33
00:03:12,359 --> 00:03:13,652
He needed to know

34
00:03:13,777 --> 00:03:16,029
how much control
he had over his victims

35
00:03:16,113 --> 00:03:17,614
before he could use it
against the 12 agents.

36
00:03:19,700 --> 00:03:24,037
I suspect Kira had to be one of the people
being investigated by the FBI,

37
00:03:24,162 --> 00:03:26,790
between the 14th and the 19th of December.

38
00:03:27,165 --> 00:03:28,750
-In fact, I have no doubt.
-[man groans]

39
00:03:31,002 --> 00:03:32,129
[grunts]

40
00:03:32,921 --> 00:03:35,257
AN IMPORTANT WITNESS
NAOMI MISORA

41
00:03:35,549 --> 00:03:36,883
Raye Penber's fiancée?

42
00:03:37,676 --> 00:03:39,344
Naomi Misora.

43
00:03:40,262 --> 00:03:41,263
So, it's her.

44
00:03:41,596 --> 00:03:43,014
She was working under me.

45
00:03:43,140 --> 00:03:45,934
I guess she must have come to Japan
with her fiancée.

46
00:03:46,518 --> 00:03:48,520
I heard she was seen with Penber.

47
00:03:49,938 --> 00:03:52,274
It's possible
that she may have found a lead.

48
00:03:52,399 --> 00:03:53,525
If that's the case,

49
00:03:53,608 --> 00:03:55,902
did Kira manage to get to her first?

50
00:04:02,617 --> 00:04:04,536
LIGHT YAGAMI

51
00:04:04,661 --> 00:04:07,330
[L] Everyone, at this point
I'd like to focus our investigation

52
00:04:07,581 --> 00:04:10,208
on only those people
who Raye Penber was tailing.

53
00:04:11,293 --> 00:04:12,627
There are two groups.

54
00:04:12,961 --> 00:04:14,755
Deputy Director Kitamura,

55
00:04:14,838 --> 00:04:16,757
as well as Detective Superintendent Yagami

56
00:04:16,840 --> 00:04:18,091
and their families.

57
00:04:19,050 --> 00:04:22,804
At this stage, I'd like to place wiretaps
and surveillance cameras

58
00:04:22,888 --> 00:04:24,556
in both households.

59
00:04:24,681 --> 00:04:26,099
That's my son you're talking about.

60
00:04:26,224 --> 00:04:28,393
Are you honestly telling me
that you suspect him?

61
00:04:28,602 --> 00:04:30,061
I do suspect him.

62
00:04:30,395 --> 00:04:32,314
CONTACT WITH LIGHT YAGAMI

63
00:04:33,607 --> 00:04:35,025
I want to tell you I'm L.

64
00:04:41,948 --> 00:04:42,991
[L] Relax, Light.

65
00:04:43,074 --> 00:04:45,035
While it's true that Kira hates losing,

66
00:04:45,160 --> 00:04:48,330
it's also true that most people
would rather win than lose.

67
00:04:48,705 --> 00:04:49,873
It's human nature.

68
00:04:50,999 --> 00:04:53,794
Look at that. He's going for the win.

69
00:04:53,877 --> 00:04:57,798
I suspect that you, Light Yagami,
are in fact Kira.

70
00:04:59,674 --> 00:05:01,551
[chuckles] You think I'm Kira?

71
00:05:02,844 --> 00:05:03,929
Ryuga,

72
00:05:04,721 --> 00:05:07,140
what would it take to get you
to believe that I'm not Kira?

73
00:05:07,390 --> 00:05:08,934
Please, isn't there something?

74
00:05:09,017 --> 00:05:10,352
If you are not Kira,

75
00:05:10,435 --> 00:05:13,563
that truth will be revealed.
Just let things run their course.

76
00:05:17,359 --> 00:05:20,529
KIRA MURDERS
USING A TELEVISION STATION

77
00:05:20,612 --> 00:05:21,696
MESSAGE FROM KIRA
4 VIDEOS

78
00:05:21,780 --> 00:05:23,615
[director] Our audience rating
should go up 60,

79
00:05:23,740 --> 00:05:26,409
no, more like 70 percent
after this!

80
00:05:26,535 --> 00:05:29,496
[newscaster] It contained a prediction
of two deaths, proving that he is Kira.

81
00:05:29,579 --> 00:05:33,083
We understand that the 2nd tape contains
a message to all people of the world.

82
00:05:33,500 --> 00:05:34,543
[Kira] I am Kira.

83
00:05:34,668 --> 00:05:36,962
The news anchor, Mr. Kazuhiko Hibima,

84
00:05:37,045 --> 00:05:39,673
will die of a heart attack
at exactly six o'clock.

85
00:05:39,756 --> 00:05:41,049
Stop this broadcast!

86
00:05:41,258 --> 00:05:42,425
We can't let him finish!

87
00:05:43,385 --> 00:05:44,261
You idiots!

88
00:05:44,636 --> 00:05:46,763
-[heart beating loudly]
-[groans]

89
00:05:46,972 --> 00:05:47,973
[Matsuda] Ukita!

90
00:05:48,139 --> 00:05:50,851
You told us that Kira
couldn't kill without a name!

91
00:05:50,934 --> 00:05:52,769
[L] But from what we've just seen,

92
00:05:52,853 --> 00:05:56,898
I'd say it's not entirely impossible
that Kira can kill with only a face.

93
00:06:00,068 --> 00:06:02,487
This is the police!
Stop this broadcast now!

94
00:06:03,071 --> 00:06:06,366
[L] There's a strong possibility
that this Kira is a fake.

95
00:06:06,449 --> 00:06:09,536
No, we should think of him
more as a Second Kira.

96
00:06:10,203 --> 00:06:11,246
Mr. Yagami.

97
00:06:11,705 --> 00:06:14,624
I'd like your permission to ask your son
to cooperate with us

98
00:06:14,708 --> 00:06:15,792
in this investigation.

99
00:06:15,876 --> 00:06:18,003
LIGHT YAGAMI IS SUMMONED
TO TASK FORCE HEADQUARTERS

100
00:06:18,086 --> 00:06:20,672
At the very least, I'd say
this isn't the Kira we are familiar with.

101
00:06:21,214 --> 00:06:24,426
That's almost exactly
how L, I mean Ryuzaki, said it.

102
00:06:24,551 --> 00:06:25,719
[Kira] When we meet,

103
00:06:25,844 --> 00:06:29,097
we can confirm our identities
by showing our Shinigami to each other.

104
00:06:29,848 --> 00:06:32,100
[screaming]

105
00:06:32,225 --> 00:06:35,604
[L] If there's a message here
written in some code that only people

106
00:06:35,729 --> 00:06:38,231
who have this Shinigami power
can understand,

107
00:06:38,315 --> 00:06:40,817
there'd be no way for me to decipher it.

108
00:06:40,942 --> 00:06:42,903
Still, it would only make sense for us

109
00:06:42,986 --> 00:06:45,947
to look into all of the places
that were mentioned in the journal.

110
00:06:46,114 --> 00:06:47,657
When you two are working together,

111
00:06:47,741 --> 00:06:50,243
I want you to keep a close eye on Light
the entire time.

112
00:06:50,368 --> 00:06:52,704
It's only a slim chance,
but if Light is Kira,

113
00:06:52,787 --> 00:06:54,831
then there's still a possibility
that the Second Kira

114
00:06:54,915 --> 00:06:56,833
may try to contact him somehow.

115
00:06:56,958 --> 00:07:00,462
Also, Mr. Yagami, please ask Mr. Mogi
to start following Light,

116
00:07:00,545 --> 00:07:02,923
so we can keep tabs
on what he's doing.

117
00:07:03,048 --> 00:07:05,342
MISA AMANE ARRESTED UNDER SUSPICION
OF BEING THE SECOND KIRA

118
00:07:06,176 --> 00:07:07,886
Light! There you are!

119
00:07:07,969 --> 00:07:09,721
Hi there. I'm Light's girlfriend.

120
00:07:09,804 --> 00:07:11,556
Misa Amane. Nice to meet you.

121
00:07:11,640 --> 00:07:13,433
-I'm Hideki Ryuga.
-Huh?

122
00:07:13,558 --> 00:07:14,935
Hideki Ryuga?

123
00:07:15,060 --> 00:07:17,103
[L] I'm not exactly sure
how you will take this,

124
00:07:17,187 --> 00:07:19,397
but regarding Misa Amane,
there's something you should know.

125
00:07:19,606 --> 00:07:23,318
We've taken her into custody
under suspicion of being the Second Kira.

126
00:07:23,568 --> 00:07:24,861
We gathered physical evidence

127
00:07:24,945 --> 00:07:26,988
from the envelopes
sent by the Second Kira.

128
00:07:27,072 --> 00:07:29,616
In particular, hairs and fibers
caught in the masking tape

129
00:07:29,741 --> 00:07:30,784
used to seal them.

130
00:07:30,951 --> 00:07:32,994
They matched what we found in Misa's room.

131
00:07:33,119 --> 00:07:34,913
MISA AMANE'S CONFINEMENT

132
00:07:35,246 --> 00:07:37,582
[Yagami] Ryuzaki!
What's the meaning of this?

133
00:07:38,500 --> 00:07:40,168
Now, hurry up and kill me!

134
00:07:40,251 --> 00:07:42,921
If you wanted to, you could kill me
right, now, couldn't you?

135
00:07:43,004 --> 00:07:45,006
[L] Does that mean
you admit to being the Second Kira?

136
00:07:45,131 --> 00:07:46,925
-Is this the reason you wish to die?
-[Misa] No!

137
00:07:47,050 --> 00:07:49,177
[Misa] I don't know anything
about the Second Kira!

138
00:07:49,260 --> 00:07:51,429
LIGHT YAGAMI IS CONFINED
AT HIS OWN REQUEST

139
00:07:51,513 --> 00:07:53,306
Ryuzaki, like I said over the phone,

140
00:07:53,723 --> 00:07:55,392
I could be Kira.

141
00:07:56,434 --> 00:07:58,770
[L] Why come here to announce
that you could be Kira?

142
00:07:59,354 --> 00:08:01,982
It's an act.
There's no "could be" about it.

143
00:08:02,107 --> 00:08:03,441
You are Kira.

144
00:08:04,109 --> 00:08:05,944
[L] Light, are you feeling okay?

145
00:08:06,069 --> 00:08:08,655
Yeah. I know I must look
pretty bad in here,

146
00:08:08,738 --> 00:08:10,490
with this useless pride...

147
00:08:10,824 --> 00:08:12,534
I suppose I'll have to...

148
00:08:13,660 --> 00:08:14,619
get rid of it!

149
00:08:15,328 --> 00:08:16,287
Ryuzaki!

150
00:08:16,454 --> 00:08:18,915
I realize I was the one
pushing for confinement,

151
00:08:19,040 --> 00:08:20,583
and that I asked you to put me in here,

152
00:08:20,834 --> 00:08:22,627
But this whole thing
is completely pointless!

153
00:08:22,752 --> 00:08:23,712
I'm not Kira!

154
00:08:23,837 --> 00:08:25,422
You have to get me out of here!

155
00:08:25,588 --> 00:08:26,548
I just heard.

156
00:08:26,631 --> 00:08:29,050
Two weeks’ worth of criminals
were just murdered all at once!

157
00:08:29,217 --> 00:08:30,093
It happened yesterday!

158
00:08:30,176 --> 00:08:31,094
KIRA RETURNS

159
00:08:31,428 --> 00:08:33,805
I don't understand what's going on here.

160
00:08:33,930 --> 00:08:35,849
TWO PEOPLE RELEASED

161
00:08:36,307 --> 00:08:39,519
I-- I'm not sure how much more of this
the three of them can take.

162
00:08:39,644 --> 00:08:42,439
Ryuzaki, you have no reason
to keep Light locked up anymore!

163
00:08:42,731 --> 00:08:44,441
It's already been fifty days.

164
00:08:47,110 --> 00:08:49,404
I'm going to kill you here
and then kill myself.

165
00:08:49,529 --> 00:08:51,531
What? What are you talking about, Dad?

166
00:08:51,614 --> 00:08:53,324
-That's crazy!
-Don't say that.

167
00:08:53,533 --> 00:08:54,784
[Yagami] It's too late.

168
00:08:55,076 --> 00:08:57,203
Please, stop, Dad. I'm not Kira!

169
00:08:57,954 --> 00:08:59,497
Light, my son...

170
00:08:59,831 --> 00:09:01,833
-From one murderer to another...
-No, Dad!

171
00:09:01,958 --> 00:09:03,376
I'll see you in Hell.

172
00:09:04,252 --> 00:09:05,920
No! Stop it!

173
00:09:06,087 --> 00:09:07,380
[gunshot]

174
00:09:07,505 --> 00:09:08,590
[cawing]

175
00:09:11,426 --> 00:09:13,803
[L] It was
a convincing performance.

176
00:09:14,137 --> 00:09:16,723
As we discussed,
I will end their confinement immediately.

177
00:09:16,890 --> 00:09:19,726
LIGHT YAGAMI IS SUMMONED AGAIN
TO HELP WITH THE INVESTIGATION

178
00:09:19,809 --> 00:09:22,854
As for you part in this agreement, Light,
you and I will be together 24-7.

179
00:09:23,438 --> 00:09:26,775
And that's how it will be
until we have brought Kira to justice.

180
00:09:26,900 --> 00:09:28,818
[grunting]

181
00:09:29,152 --> 00:09:30,570
[Misa gasping]

182
00:09:30,779 --> 00:09:31,988
YOTSUBA

183
00:09:32,072 --> 00:09:34,699
[Light] Their deaths have all worked
in Yotsuba's favor.

184
00:09:34,824 --> 00:09:35,700
Looking back,

185
00:09:35,867 --> 00:09:39,037
there've been 13 similar deaths
in the past three months.

186
00:09:39,120 --> 00:09:41,039
INVESTIGATION AND INFILTRATION
OF YOTSUBA

187
00:09:41,164 --> 00:09:43,750
[L] Is Kira someone from Yotsuba?
Or is Kira simply using Yotsuba?

188
00:09:43,917 --> 00:09:45,126
I haven't figured that out yet,

189
00:09:45,251 --> 00:09:48,379
but we'll proceed under the assumption
that this is Kira's doing.

190
00:09:48,797 --> 00:09:50,840
We will focus on Yotsuba.

191
00:09:50,965 --> 00:09:52,842
Please be sure not to act impulsively,

192
00:09:52,967 --> 00:09:54,302
out of panic or haste,

193
00:09:54,427 --> 00:09:56,221
and don't take matters
into your own hands.

194
00:09:56,304 --> 00:09:58,807
My name is Taro Matsui.
I'm an agent with Yoshida Productions!

195
00:09:58,932 --> 00:09:59,933
Would you be interested

196
00:10:00,100 --> 00:10:02,060
in using Misa Amane
as your new spokesperson?

197
00:10:02,685 --> 00:10:04,104
Ryuzaki, are you watching this?

198
00:10:04,270 --> 00:10:06,272
The eight men who came here
were having a meeting to decide

199
00:10:06,397 --> 00:10:09,025
-who'd they get Kira to kill for them.
-[L] If Matsuda dies,

200
00:10:09,192 --> 00:10:11,945
our suspicions about the Yotsuba group
would be confirmed.

201
00:10:12,028 --> 00:10:14,072
[Matsuda] Do you think there’s anything
I can do to save myself?

202
00:10:14,280 --> 00:10:15,698
[L] Matsuda, you idiot.

203
00:10:15,782 --> 00:10:18,326
KYOSUKE HIGUCHI CONFIRMED AS KIRA

204
00:10:18,743 --> 00:10:20,245
Good luck, Misa-Misa!

205
00:10:20,453 --> 00:10:24,040
I'll be here ready to celebrate
when they decide to hire you!

206
00:10:24,165 --> 00:10:26,668
It's always been my dream
to become Kira's wife.

207
00:10:26,751 --> 00:10:29,379
-I know he'll need me by his side.
-Huh?

208
00:10:29,796 --> 00:10:30,922
And you know why?

209
00:10:31,005 --> 00:10:32,632
Because I'm the Second Kira.

210
00:10:32,757 --> 00:10:33,925
[laughs]

211
00:10:34,050 --> 00:10:37,804
Well, since I happen to be Kira,
does that mean you'll marry me, Misa?

212
00:10:37,971 --> 00:10:39,639
So, based on what he said,

213
00:10:39,722 --> 00:10:41,349
Higuchi is Kira!

214
00:10:41,516 --> 00:10:42,684
THE PLAN TO CAPTURE HIGUCHI
IS SET IN MOTION

215
00:10:42,767 --> 00:10:45,145
-[Matsuda] So, what are you gonna do?
-[L] I'm going to trick Higuchi

216
00:10:45,228 --> 00:10:47,355
-using Sakura TV.
-Like a hidden camera show!

217
00:10:47,480 --> 00:10:49,691
Higuchi, we've got a problem.
Turn on the television.

218
00:10:50,650 --> 00:10:51,568
Hm?

219
00:10:51,651 --> 00:10:54,279
[man 1] So, you're saying
one of those people is Kira, right?

220
00:10:54,362 --> 00:10:57,073
[man 2]Yes. I've got a lot of evidence
to prove it, too. [yelps]

221
00:10:58,950 --> 00:11:00,034
[Higuchi] It-- It's him!

222
00:11:00,243 --> 00:11:02,120
Why is he still alive?

223
00:11:03,705 --> 00:11:05,498
[tires screeching]

224
00:11:05,582 --> 00:11:07,584
I see Higuchi. I'm in pursuit.

225
00:11:08,209 --> 00:11:09,502
We're heading after him!

226
00:11:13,256 --> 00:11:14,174
[siren wailing]

227
00:11:14,257 --> 00:11:15,592
You in the red car.

228
00:11:15,675 --> 00:11:18,303
Pull over to the side of the road. Now!

229
00:11:18,761 --> 00:11:20,555
[Higuchi] Rem. Let's make the deal.

230
00:11:20,680 --> 00:11:21,556
A deal?

231
00:11:22,056 --> 00:11:23,224
You were speeding.

232
00:11:23,308 --> 00:11:24,642
License, please!

233
00:11:24,767 --> 00:11:25,894
Yeah, no problem.

234
00:11:28,897 --> 00:11:29,814
[officer 1] Hey!

235
00:11:29,939 --> 00:11:32,358
[officer 2] Higuchi ditched the cop
He's driving away!

236
00:11:32,442 --> 00:11:33,484
This is traffic control.

237
00:11:33,610 --> 00:11:34,819
-[heartbeat]
-[groans]

238
00:11:36,321 --> 00:11:39,991
Everyone! It's too dangerous
to allow further action by Higuchi!

239
00:11:40,116 --> 00:11:41,492
Let's bring him in!

240
00:11:41,659 --> 00:11:44,329
I believe he has the same powers
as the Second Kira,

241
00:11:44,829 --> 00:11:47,457
He is able to kill
just by looking at someone's face.

242
00:11:47,540 --> 00:11:50,460
Please, keep this in mind
when you move in to arrest him.

243
00:11:50,543 --> 00:11:52,712
-[tires screeching]
-[grunting]

244
00:11:53,963 --> 00:11:55,506
Stop right there!

245
00:11:56,424 --> 00:11:57,467
[tires screeching]

246
00:11:58,676 --> 00:12:00,345
Stay back!
Stay back or I'll shoot!

247
00:12:00,428 --> 00:12:01,721
-I swear! [yells]
-[gunshot]

248
00:12:03,473 --> 00:12:04,599
HIGUCHI'S CAPTURE

249
00:12:04,682 --> 00:12:07,101
[L] Higuchi, how were you able
to kill people?

250
00:12:07,352 --> 00:12:10,897
You probably won't believe me,
but I've got a special notebook.

251
00:12:11,064 --> 00:12:13,274
If I write someone's name in it
while thinking of their face,

252
00:12:13,358 --> 00:12:14,484
that person dies.

253
00:12:14,692 --> 00:12:17,403
[Yagami] It was in one of the compartments
of Higuchi's bag.

254
00:12:17,528 --> 00:12:18,780
[Yagami screaming]

255
00:12:19,322 --> 00:12:20,823
[L] What' is it, Mr. Yagami?

256
00:12:21,950 --> 00:12:24,077
[Yagami] It's a monster!

257
00:12:28,581 --> 00:12:29,749
A Shinigami…

258
00:12:30,083 --> 00:12:33,211
There have to be two notebooks!
Possibly more!

259
00:12:33,544 --> 00:12:34,921
This isn't over yet.

260
00:12:35,088 --> 00:12:37,131
THE DEATH NOTE AND AN INQUIRY
INTO ITS RULES

261
00:12:38,049 --> 00:12:39,759
[Aizawa] "How to use it..."

262
00:12:40,051 --> 00:12:42,762
It says: "The human whose name is written
in this notebook,

263
00:12:43,096 --> 00:12:44,347
shall die."

264
00:12:45,139 --> 00:12:47,976
And then, there's this last rule...

265
00:12:48,434 --> 00:12:51,271
According to this,
"If the person using the note

266
00:12:51,562 --> 00:12:54,691
fails to consecutively write names
of people to be killed,

267
00:12:54,857 --> 00:12:57,110
-within 13 days of each other..."
-[L] ...within 13 days of each other,

268
00:12:57,235 --> 00:12:58,945
then the user will die."

269
00:12:59,487 --> 00:13:02,448
Light Yagami and Misa Amane
are both still alive.

270
00:13:03,199 --> 00:13:04,909
Thirteen days.

271
00:13:05,576 --> 00:13:06,953
That's the only problem.

272
00:13:13,418 --> 00:13:16,004
The following is the record,
which contains everything

273
00:13:16,129 --> 00:13:18,631
I have investigated on the Kira Incident.

274
00:13:20,049 --> 00:13:22,218
The fact that now you are reading
this message,

275
00:13:22,302 --> 00:13:24,887
means I am no longer alive at this moment.

276
00:13:27,265 --> 00:13:30,685
I hereby leave this record
as my firm achievement.

277
00:13:31,811 --> 00:13:32,937
That is all.

278
00:13:38,568 --> 00:13:43,531
[continuous beep]

279
00:14:06,596 --> 00:14:08,765
[Matsuda] It's been ten days
since Ryuzaki's funeral.

280
00:14:09,057 --> 00:14:11,059
It looks like we
are not gonna die after all.

281
00:14:12,060 --> 00:14:13,936
We know Watari's true identity now,

282
00:14:14,020 --> 00:14:16,856
but we never found out
anything about who Ryuzaki really was.

283
00:14:16,981 --> 00:14:17,982
Yeah, that's true.

284
00:14:18,149 --> 00:14:20,902
Who could have guessed that Watari
was actually a famous inventor.

285
00:14:21,444 --> 00:14:24,197
The paper says he founded orphanages
around the world

286
00:14:24,280 --> 00:14:26,616
using the fortune
he inherited from his patents.

287
00:14:26,866 --> 00:14:28,826
[Matsuda] He was a fine man. A hero!

288
00:14:29,285 --> 00:14:30,703
But it doesn't help us now.

289
00:14:30,828 --> 00:14:33,664
We can't continue investigating
using this place as our base

290
00:14:33,790 --> 00:14:35,166
with L and Watari gone.

291
00:14:35,333 --> 00:14:36,334
This is tough.

292
00:14:36,542 --> 00:14:38,795
[Yagami] Hmm. Light, how's it going?

293
00:14:39,629 --> 00:14:42,298
I should be able to transfer the system
and most of the information

294
00:14:42,382 --> 00:14:43,883
out of here by tonight.

295
00:14:44,092 --> 00:14:45,259
It's weird, though.

296
00:14:45,426 --> 00:14:47,220
I almost feel as if I'm stealing.

297
00:14:47,678 --> 00:14:50,640
I've created a voice filter
identical to the one Ryuzaki used.

298
00:14:50,765 --> 00:14:53,184
We can use it
to make the police think he is still alive

299
00:14:53,309 --> 00:14:55,645
and give them orders
like we've doing so far, but…

300
00:14:56,270 --> 00:14:58,356
Who's going to take the place of L?

301
00:14:58,481 --> 00:14:59,857
Where he will work from?

302
00:15:00,108 --> 00:15:01,859
And what do we do with the notebook?

303
00:15:01,943 --> 00:15:03,653
Come on.
What are you talking about, Light?

304
00:15:03,861 --> 00:15:06,364
You're the only one
who can take on the role of L.

305
00:15:06,531 --> 00:15:07,615
[Light] Hm.

306
00:15:09,784 --> 00:15:10,993
[Light] I don't know.

307
00:15:11,077 --> 00:15:13,663
Ryuzaki was killed by Kira
because he challenged him.

308
00:15:14,122 --> 00:15:16,124
That's not something I'm eager to do.

309
00:15:16,207 --> 00:15:19,001
Besides, I would be fooling
the people of the world.

310
00:15:19,168 --> 00:15:20,795
I can understand how you feel,

311
00:15:20,878 --> 00:15:23,005
but you're really the only one of us
who can do this.

312
00:15:23,256 --> 00:15:25,550
That's right.
Even Ryuzaki said so himself.

313
00:15:26,008 --> 00:15:28,344
You would be capable of succeeding L.

314
00:15:30,888 --> 00:15:32,181
[Light] Just as I thought.

315
00:15:32,265 --> 00:15:33,683
It's too simple.

316
00:15:33,933 --> 00:15:36,060
It's no fun without Ryuzaki here.

317
00:15:37,311 --> 00:15:38,312
[Light] I understand.

318
00:15:38,396 --> 00:15:39,730
All right. I'll do it.

319
00:15:41,315 --> 00:15:43,568
But... I won't be like Ryuzaki.

320
00:15:43,651 --> 00:15:45,027
I won't take big risks

321
00:15:45,111 --> 00:15:47,488
like challenging Kira directly
to gather clues.

322
00:15:47,613 --> 00:15:48,573
It's just not me.

323
00:15:48,865 --> 00:15:52,076
Yeah, it's probably better
if we play it safe.

324
00:15:52,201 --> 00:15:54,912
Ryuzaki may have been
a little too confrontational.

325
00:15:55,037 --> 00:15:56,080
[Light] In that case…

326
00:15:56,247 --> 00:15:59,750
I'll be able to do the same sort of work,
using both this computer and my own.

327
00:15:59,834 --> 00:16:00,835
In fact,

328
00:16:00,918 --> 00:16:03,921
it'll be possible for me to act as L
in the comfort of my own room.

329
00:16:04,630 --> 00:16:06,382
I can be Watari as well.

330
00:16:07,175 --> 00:16:10,178
But it'll be difficult to pull off
with Mum and Sayu around.

331
00:16:11,429 --> 00:16:14,098
Things would be easier
if I could rent a one-bedroom apartment.

332
00:16:14,265 --> 00:16:15,850
Well, considering your age,

333
00:16:15,933 --> 00:16:19,187
it certainly wouldn't look odd to anyone
if I let you move out on your own.

334
00:16:19,562 --> 00:16:22,356
Hey, yeah! And then we'll be able
to use Light's new apartment

335
00:16:22,440 --> 00:16:23,691
as our taskforce headquarters.

336
00:16:23,774 --> 00:16:25,193
-That's a great idea!
-[Yagami] Hm.

337
00:16:25,610 --> 00:16:28,863
All that's left to figure out now
is what to do with the notebook.

338
00:16:28,946 --> 00:16:30,781
[Light] It's really not that difficult.

339
00:16:31,866 --> 00:16:33,034
There's five of us here.

340
00:16:33,117 --> 00:16:35,161
And we know none of us
will ever use the notebook.

341
00:16:35,328 --> 00:16:37,413
We'll just have one of us take it
and hide it somewhere

342
00:16:37,497 --> 00:16:39,373
where no one else can ever get to it.

343
00:16:41,000 --> 00:16:43,085
Please, Chief, it's gotta be you.

344
00:16:43,169 --> 00:16:45,421
Yeah, Chief! We can count on you!

345
00:16:45,630 --> 00:16:48,716
You're a pillar of justice, after all.
[nervous laughter]

346
00:16:48,841 --> 00:16:50,051
You want me to...

347
00:16:51,093 --> 00:16:51,969
All right.

348
00:16:52,553 --> 00:16:54,597
We'll avenge Ryuzaki together!

349
00:16:55,515 --> 00:16:58,142
Yeah. Kira's still out there somewhere.

350
00:16:58,309 --> 00:16:59,810
We'll catch him. That's a promise.

351
00:17:00,102 --> 00:17:01,145
-Mm-hmm.
-Mm-hmm.

352
00:17:01,521 --> 00:17:03,439
[Matsuda] Well then, why don't we
have a little party

353
00:17:03,523 --> 00:17:05,483
to celebrate Light becoming
L number two?

354
00:17:05,608 --> 00:17:08,194
[Aizawa] Quit fooling around.
Now's not the time for stuff like that.

355
00:17:08,361 --> 00:17:09,570
[Yagami] Let's take it easy.

356
00:17:17,411 --> 00:17:18,454
[Misa] Light!

357
00:17:18,913 --> 00:17:20,831
This is our first date in forever.

358
00:17:20,957 --> 00:17:22,917
Can't you enjoy yourself a little more?

359
00:17:25,795 --> 00:17:26,754
[Light] Misa…

360
00:17:28,839 --> 00:17:30,800
-Let's move in together.
-[Misa gasps]

361
00:17:32,093 --> 00:17:33,261
You mean it?

362
00:17:33,636 --> 00:17:35,763
[Light] Yeah. I've already rented a place.

363
00:17:35,930 --> 00:17:36,973
[gasps]

364
00:17:37,306 --> 00:17:39,767
[screams] Yay! Victory is mine!

365
00:17:39,850 --> 00:17:41,352
Misa wins!

366
00:17:41,435 --> 00:17:44,230
-[Ryuk] Victory?
-[Misa] Over Kiyomi and Mari and Yuri.

367
00:17:44,647 --> 00:17:46,649
But it's all right, now. Don't worry.

368
00:17:46,732 --> 00:17:49,193
I knew you were
just using those other girls to trick L.

369
00:17:49,443 --> 00:17:51,779
You don't have any reason
to see them anymore, right?

370
00:17:52,947 --> 00:17:53,990
[Light] Right...

371
00:18:01,664 --> 00:18:03,499
Hey. Now that L's dead,

372
00:18:03,583 --> 00:18:06,127
does that mean
you've finally settled the score with him?

373
00:18:06,586 --> 00:18:07,461
[Light] Yeah.

374
00:18:08,087 --> 00:18:11,465
So, in that case, I guess things
are gonna get pretty boring from now on.

375
00:18:14,343 --> 00:18:16,178
[Light] That's not true, Ryuk.

376
00:18:17,597 --> 00:18:19,098
From this moment on...

377
00:18:20,391 --> 00:18:23,227
I'll show you the creation
of the new world.

378
00:18:23,894 --> 00:18:24,854
Huh?

379
00:18:24,937 --> 00:18:26,606
[lightning crackles]

380
00:18:27,064 --> 00:18:28,941
[thunder rumbling]

381
00:19:07,605 --> 00:19:13,444
[inaudible]

382
00:19:23,537 --> 00:19:24,413
[gasps, groans]

383
00:19:24,580 --> 00:19:26,290
-[cat meows loudly]
-[tires screeching]

384
00:19:26,624 --> 00:19:28,292
[crashing]

385
00:19:35,716 --> 00:19:36,717
Daddy!

386
00:19:39,011 --> 00:19:40,179
-[thud]
-[glass breaking]

387
00:19:40,971 --> 00:19:41,972
[child] Daddy?

388
00:19:51,482 --> 00:19:53,275
This will be the rebirth of Yotsuba.

389
00:19:53,567 --> 00:19:55,611
Yeah. It's a new start.

390
00:19:55,820 --> 00:19:57,029
-Huh?
-[man groans]

391
00:19:57,196 --> 00:19:59,490
Namikawa? What's wrong?

392
00:20:00,908 --> 00:20:02,576
Huh? That's impossible!

393
00:20:02,702 --> 00:20:04,995
-[loud heartbeat]
-[groans]

394
00:20:08,624 --> 00:20:11,502
[man] In April 2012, Light Yagami, age 23,

395
00:20:11,585 --> 00:20:13,963
joined Japan's National Police Agency.

396
00:20:14,046 --> 00:20:15,798
In the summer of 2012,

397
00:20:15,923 --> 00:20:18,926
Kira's killings increased
at an unprecedented rate.

398
00:20:19,009 --> 00:20:21,762
Numerous people around the world
were terrified of Kira,

399
00:20:21,971 --> 00:20:25,141
and yet, there were just as many
cheering him on.

400
00:20:25,307 --> 00:20:27,935
Gradually, their private thoughts
became public opinion,

401
00:20:28,018 --> 00:20:31,355
and soon, certain nations
began to accept Kira's judgement.

402
00:20:32,815 --> 00:20:34,942
The world was heading into a dark age

403
00:20:35,025 --> 00:20:37,611
in which Kira's will was the only law.

404
00:20:43,117 --> 00:20:45,703
[beeping]

405
00:20:56,130 --> 00:20:59,049
-[birds chirping]
-[children playing]

406
00:21:16,609 --> 00:21:17,860
[man] What is it, Roger?

407
00:21:22,907 --> 00:21:23,866
It's L.

408
00:21:23,949 --> 00:21:24,867
He's dead.

409
00:21:26,368 --> 00:21:33,375
TO BE CONTINUED

410
00:21:49,850 --> 00:21:51,894
[theme music playing]
